---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import BoxedContent from '../components/BoxedContent.astro'
import FluidContent from '../components/FluidContent.astro'
import MyAge from '../components/MyAge.astro'
import MySkills from '../components/MySkills.astro'
import type { SEOData } from '../types/SEO'
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets'

import imageFlori from '../assets/images/flori.jpg'
import imageKids from '../assets/images/cute_toddler_girl_and_cute_baby_boy_as_software_engineers.jpg'
import imageFloriAtWork from '../assets/images/flori_infoflow_live.jpg'

/// Page title
const title = 'About'

/// OpenGraph meta tags data
const seo: SEOData = {
  head: {
    title,
    description: 'As web developer I do a Vue things.',
  },
  og: {
    type: 'website',
  },
}
---

<Layout seo={seo}>
  <main>
    <BoxedContent>
      <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-black">About me</h1>

      <p class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">
        <span class="highlight">tl;dr</span> Florian van der GaliÃ«n: Letting coding
        agents create things.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl text-balance lg:mb-12">
        Here, I'll share who I am, what I do for a living, and what inspires me
        most.
      </p>
    </BoxedContent>

    <FluidContent>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-12 md:flex-row">
        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">
            Hi, I'm Florian van der GaliÃ«n.
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
            I'm a <MyAge /> web developer who loves working with <span
              class="highlight">Vue.js</span
            >, <span class="highlight">Astro</span>, Tailwind CSS, <span
              class="highlight">Bun</span
            >, TypeScript, Supabase but also SQLite and <span class="highlight"
              >Drizzle</span
            >. Lately, I've been exploring AI-assisted <span class="highlight"
              >agentic coding</span
            > (<span class="slanted">embrace the vibe</span> ðŸ˜‰)â€”having AI agents
            help me build things is pretty fun. I enjoy creating fast, modern web
            apps that work well and look good.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="relative aspect-9/10 w-full flex-none rotate-2 overflow-hidden rounded-xl sm:w-72 sm:rounded-2xl"
        >
          <Picture
            alt="Florian van der GaliÃ«n"
            src={imageFlori}
            densities={[1, 2, 3]}
            width={300}
            height={300}
            class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </FluidContent>

    <BoxedContent>
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">My 9 to 5</h2>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        I work at <a
          href="https://www.tmt.de"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="link highlight">TMT</a
        >, the Bayreuth-based IT-, Internet- and media specialist with more than
        50 colleagues covering managed IT, cyber security, enterprise networks,
        fiber internet, hosting, bespoke web services, design, digital signage,
        plus TV & video production.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        Together with the Stadtwerke Bayreuth we run a <span class="highlight"
          >regional fiber backbone</span
        >
        that feeds our data centers and products like the AI knowledge platform <a
          href="https://www.tmt-infoflow.de"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="link highlight font-semibold">iNFOFLOW</a
        >, giving clients secure connectivity and cloud workflows end to end.
        I'm part of the Web Dev & AI unit, so my day-to-day is all about
        crafting modern websites, mobile apps, and AI solutions that merge TMT's
        creative and infrastructure teams.
      </p>

      <figure class="mb-8">
        <div class="group relative mt-8 mb-16">
          <Picture
            alt="Me, Florian van der GaliÃ«n, at an event representing our product iNFOFLOW."
            src={imageFloriAtWork}
            formats={['avif', 'webp']}
            densities={[1, 2, 3]}
            width={700}
            height={420}
            loading="lazy"
            class="-rotate-1 -skew-x-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
          />
          <div
            class="absolute right-8 bottom-0 left-8 z-10 -translate-y-8 -rotate-6 -skew-x-3 rounded bg-gray-700/90 px-4 py-2 text-white opacity-0 backdrop-blur-sm transition duration-300 group-hover:translate-y-3 group-hover:rotate-0 group-hover:opacity-100 sm:px-12 sm:py-4 dark:bg-slate-50/90 dark:text-slate-800"
          >
            <p class="text-sm leading-tight font-[450] text-pretty">
              Me, Florian van der GaliÃ«n, at an event at our offices
              representing the AI product iNFOFLOW.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="-mt-[2em]!">
          Representing our product <a
            href="https://www.tmt-infoflow.de"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="link">iNFOFLOW</a
          > at an in-house event at TMT offices.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        As a <span class="highlight">Full Stack Developer</span>, my day-to-day
        is about balancing solid <span class="highlight">Supabase</span>-powered
        backends with the kind of frontend work that makes interfaces clear and
        accessible. <span class="highlight">Astro</span>
        is my go-to for shipping fast projects, especially when I can mix Astro Islands
        with <span class="highlight">Vue</span> components to keep things modular
        and maintainable. I spend a lot of time refining detailsâ€”<span
          class="highlight">accessible</span
        > color contrast, sensible focus states, and UI patterns that feel good to
        useâ€”because a clean user experience is what keeps products useful after launch.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        Outside the app layer, I like getting my hands dirty with
        infrastructure.
        <span class="highlight">Docker</span> is my default for packaging services,
        and I keep a few personal <span class="highlight">VPS</span> projects running
        just to try new setups. Exploring
        <span class="highlight">DevOps</span> practices, wiring up <span
          class="highlight">CI pipelines</span
        >, and automating GitLab workflows scratches the same itch as building a
        good UIâ€”clean feedback loops and predictable deployments make the rest
        of the stack easier to trust.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">Loving husband, father of two</h2>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        In my personal life, I am a dedicated husband and a proud <span
          class="highlight">father of two</span
        >
        wonderful children. My children bring an immense amount of joy and fulfillment
        to my life, and they are a constant reminder of what truly matters. My family
        is my source of inspiration and motivation, and they play a significant role
        in who I am both personally and professionally.
      </p>

      <figure class="mb-8">
        <div class="group relative mt-8 mb-16">
          <Picture
            alt="Cute toddler girl and cute baby boy as software engineers in their kids playroom cartoon, flat vector illustration (MidJourney v6)"
            src={imageKids}
            formats={['avif', 'webp']}
            densities={[1, 2, 3]}
            width={700}
            height={350}
            loading="lazy"
            class="-rotate-1 -skew-x-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
          />

          <div
            class="absolute right-8 bottom-0 left-8 z-10 -translate-y-8 -rotate-6 -skew-x-3 rounded bg-gray-700/90 px-4 py-2 text-white opacity-0 backdrop-blur-sm transition duration-300 group-hover:translate-y-3 group-hover:rotate-0 group-hover:opacity-100 sm:px-12 sm:py-4 dark:bg-slate-50/90 dark:text-slate-800"
          >
            <p class="text-sm leading-tight font-[450]">
              Cute toddler girl and cute baby boy as software engineers in their
              kids playroom cartoon, flat vector illustration (MidJourney v6)
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption class="-mt-[2em]!">
          This is how I imagine my kids will be hacking things together when
          they're older.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p class="mb-8 text-xl">
        My <span class="highlight">wife</span>, once my best friend, is now my
        constant companion and the cornerstone of my life. Her support has been
        instrumental in my personal and professional growth. She challenges me,
        supports me, and inspires me in ways I never thought possible.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl">
        <span class="highlight">Thanks to my family</span>, I am not only a
        better person, but also a better coder.
      </p>
    </BoxedContent>

    <FluidContent>
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-black">Skills</h2>
      <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">
        What I do for a living? <span class="highlight">Code.</span>
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-12 text-xl">
        With a focus on Vue.js, Tailwind CSS, TypeScript and iOS development
        using Swift, I have a strong foundation in modern web and app
        development. While I'm well-versed in WordPress, I'm passionate about
        building custom solutions that deliver exceptional user experiences.
      </p>

      <MySkills />
    </FluidContent>
  </main>
</Layout>
